## Code Review Checklist

### Before Submitting PR
- [ ] **TypeScript strict mode:** No `any`, no type errors
- [ ] **Tests added/updated:** Unit tests for services, E2E for flows
- [ ] **Lint passes:** `pnpm lint` with no errors
- [ ] **Typecheck passes:** `pnpm typecheck` clean
- [ ] **i18n complete:** All user-facing strings use `t()`, translations added to `ko.json`/`en.json`/`ja.json`
- [ ] **IPC validated:** All IPC inputs validated in main process handlers
- [ ] **No console.logs:** Use proper logging (or remove debug logs)
- [ ] **Performance tested:** No blocking operations in main thread
- [ ] **Memory leaks checked:** Services properly cleaned up (`cleanup()` methods called)
- [ ] **Accessibility:** Keyboard navigation works, ARIA labels on interactive elements
- [ ] **Error handling:** All async operations wrapped in try-catch with user-friendly errors

### Reviewer Checklist
- [ ] **Code matches architecture:** Services in main, UI in renderer, no blurred boundaries
- [ ] **Security:** No exposed Node.js APIs to renderer, all IPC goes through preload
- [ ] **Testing:** Adequate coverage, tests actually test behavior (not implementation details)
- [ ] **UX:** Changes improve or maintain user experience
- [ ] **Performance:** No unnecessary re-renders, efficient algorithms
- [ ] **Documentation:** Code is self-documenting or has comments for complex logic

