## Accessibility Requirements

### Keyboard Navigation
- All interactive elements must be keyboard-accessible (Tab, Enter, Space)
- Modal dialogs must trap focus (use Radix Dialog component)
- Custom shortcuts must not conflict with OS/browser defaults

### ARIA Labels
```tsx
// тЬЕ Good
<button aria-label={t('recording.controls.start')}>
  <PlayIcon />
</button>

// тЭМ Bad (icon-only button with no label)
<button>
  <PlayIcon />
</button>
```

### Screen Reader Support
- Use semantic HTML (`<button>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, not `<div onClick>`)
- All images must have `alt` text
- Form inputs must have associated `<label>`
- Status updates must use `aria-live` regions

### Color Contrast
- Text must meet WCAG AA standards (4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text)
- Use Tailwind's default color palette (already accessible)

